the servant of a priest, or it may denote an (illegitimate) son of a priest. Compare   Labate  ."]},{"name":"Abbot","meanings":["English and Scottish: variant of   Abbott  . The spelling with one <i>-t</i> is more typically Scottish than English, and in Gaelic-speaking areas of Scotland, this is sometimes an Anglicized form of   McNabb  ."]},{"name":"Abbitt","meanings":["English: variant of   Abbott  ."]},{"name":"Abbett","meanings":["English: variant of   Abbott  ."]},{"name":"Abbotts","meanings":["English:","topographic or occupational name from Middle English <i>(atte) abbotes</i> ‘(at the, of the) abbot's (house or quarters)’, a name for someone who lived or worked at such a place, presumably a servant.","variant of   Abbott  , with post-medieval excrescent <i>-s</i>."]}]},{"name":"John","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["As a boy's name this represents a revival of Middle English <i>Jan</i>, a by‐form of   John  , or an adoption of the common European form with this spelling. As a girl's name it is a short form of names such as   Janet   and   Janice ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"John Abbott was born in 1330, in Chelsworth, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom. He had at least 1 son with Mrs. John Abbott II. He died in Suffolk, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"1330–":"1330–Surnud","1336–Female":"1336–Surnud","1435–1490":"1435–1490","1425–1490":"1425–1490","1330–Male":"1330–Surnud","1425":"1425","1435":"1435","1336":"1336","1330":"1330","1490":"1490","c.1435":"umbes 1435","Chelsworth,,,England":"Chelsworth, Suffolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Suffolk, England":"Suffolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1330–":"1330–Kuollut","1336–Female":"1336–Kuollut","1435–1490":"1435–1490","1425–1490":"1425–1490","1330–Male":"1330–Kuollut","1425":"1425","1435":"1435","1336":"1336","1330":"1330","1490":"1490","c.1435":"noin 1435","Chelsworth,,,England":"Chelsworth, Suffolk, Englanti, Yh